      "commonMisconceptions": [
        {
          "misconceptionId": "misc-03-enthusiasm-persuades",
          "misconception": "The more enthusiasm you display, the more persuasive your pitch will be \u2014 passion is contagious and will bring friends on board.",
          "whyIncorrect": "Visible enthusiasm from an expert triggers reactance in skeptics. The friend hears 'this is clearly your thing' and distances themselves. Measured, curious framing consistently outperforms evangelical passion.",
          "remediationStrategy": "Present the two-pitch contrast (enthusiasm-driven vs. curiosity-framed) for the same game. Have the learner rate each from the perspective of the resistant friend, then explain the gap. The perspective-switch is essential.",
