              "captionOrTranscript": "MEDIA PLACEHOLDER \u2014 Diagram: Five nodes in a horizontal left-to-right flow connected by arrows. Each node is a rounded rectangle with: (1) Principle name in bold; (2) one-line definition; (3) a concrete example line of dialogue in italics. Node 1: Framing \u2014 'Lead with what it feels like, not what it is.' Example: 'It's like building a startup from scratch.' Node 2: Social Proof \u2014 'Name a specific person like them who enjoyed it.' Example: 'My sister who never plays games made us play it three times.' Node 3: Commitment Threshold \u2014 'Make the yes feel tiny and reversible.' Example: 'We can stop after one round if you want.' Node 4: Loss Aversion \u2014 'A gentle, honest nudge at the end.' Example: 'You were the only one who missed last time.' Node 5: Objection Redirection \u2014 'Acknowledge, validate, redirect.' Example: 'Yeah, some games are like that \u2014 this one is different because...' Visual style: connected nodes, warm colour palette, compact enough to read in one glance."
